name: St. Dad "S/T" LP
description: Finally, the idiot genius that is the ST. DAD long player is unleashed on this stupid fucking world. These vocals are the snottiest, most crazed thing put to tape in a long time. The songs are always on the brink of falling apart, like all good early punk and hardcore was. It sounds like THE CRUCIFUCKS recorded in a bedroom if the bedroom was in a cave. No poser shit here, just 4 legit weirdos that couldn't even scan their photos in for the layout correctly. The band has been broken up for a while but all 3 labels involved (Moon Machination, 16oh, and Vinyl Rites) knew it had to become part of our reality. You're welcome, world, you probably didn't ask for it.

name: Acid Problem - S/T 12"
description: "Acid Problem have emerged from Brooklyn with a stellar 12‚Äù e.p that combines the experimentation and tangential riffs of later era Black Flag with the powerful driving song structures of more modern offerings like Condominium or Slices. Not afraid to take a walk on the demented side these 5 songs still remain white-knuckle gripped to pounding guitar lines in a centrifuge of frantic hc punk sensibilities. Fans of hc punk ranging from Cold Sweat to early Flipper will find an immediate bond with this release from 16oh records. Elements of this s/t effort verge toward straight up pounding hc punk only to turn upon itself in a possessed ferocity as if constantly at war with itself. Any listener duped into feeling this is another straightforward hc release is soon jolted by frenetic unease and palpable agitation that make any moments of ease not only unattainable but unimaginable. Impossible to pigeon-hole but immensely satisfying this is a debut that compels you to re-set the needle as soon as it ends." - Richard Boe Stream the entire record here: Acid Problem on bandcamp

name: Crime Desire "ID Music To Combat The Super Ego"
description: After spending about a year working on getting this to look and sound exactly the way it should, the Crime Desire LP "Id Music To Combat The Superego" is now ready to go. The 10-song full length LP comes in a thick "tip-on"/"Japanese HC"/ "60's" style (whichever you like to call it) jacket with a screen printed OBI strip and inner lyric sleeve on 140g vinyl mastered by Alan Douches. What's the music like? Influences come from groups like Burn, Gauze, Chain of Strength, GISM, Randy Holden, Integrity, Rorschach, MDC, Samhain, Siege, Whitehouse, and tons of others. It doesn't mean you'll necessarily hear those bands' riffs when you play the record, but that's the kind of stuff you'll find in Crime Desire's record collections. Misanthropic lyrics and stark artwork round out a great hardcore record for anyone sick of artsy pretension and bored with straight revisionism.

name: Crime Desire "Every Day in Chains" 12"

name: Jesus Fucking Christ "Self Titled" LP
description: After playing in and around the Bay Area for a couple of years Oakland's JESUS FUCKING CHRIST makes it's recorded debut with this self titled rager. Coming off more like an old school hardcore thrash attack than the usual "Oakland sound," JESUS FUCKING CHRIST goes right for the throat. Featuring punk and metal veterans Dave Edwardson from the legendary NEUROSIS on bass and vocals and Larry from THE RICKEETS as well as LARRY AND THE GO NOWHERES on guitar and vocals. For fans of old school Northwest hardcore like the ACCUSED or POION IDEA as well as anyone looking for something like the sounds of the earliest NEUROSIS records.

name: Jesus Fucking Christ "Life's Hateful Seed"
description: Building on their Poison Idea meets the Accused sound, JESUS FUCKING CHRIST has added some metallic flourishes with a thicker guitar sound and some intense and heavy mid tempo sections. Dave Ed's (Neurosis) handled the production in house this time around. Dave's voice is more prominent on many of the tracks, going from backing vocals to a full second vocalist. Larry's guitar work has only gotten more intense with the addition of occasional frantic punk rock solos throughout the album. Lyrically, the songs lash out at everything from punk scene politics and institutions to co-workers and the city they are from while always remaining firmly in the negative. All in all, this album accomplishes what any excellent second album does: builds and expands on the framework set by the first and never disappoints. Limited to 666 copies

name: Raw Nerves LP
description: With members playing in hardcore punk bands for the better part of the last two decades, along with some younger energy and blood, Raw Nerves sound is a collection of those influences, ultimately coming back to what they know best: anger and speed. Musically, they hold a nice balance between classic early 80's hardcore like Negative Approach, Black Flag and Poison Idea to the late 80s/early 90s sounds of Citizens Arrest, Born Against, Econochrist, along with more modern bands such as Acts of Sedition, or Sacred Shock. Lyrically, they interweave boiling political dissections and intelligent sarcasm without ignoring the personal implications the fucked up world we live in has on all of us. But don't be fooled; they are not a white flag of surrender or nihilistic indulgence, but rather a call to arms. One time press of 500 and an mp3 download is included.

name: Fighting Dogs "S/T" 7"
description: "This final three-track, limited EP from this Philadelphia band refines where their previous 2004 LP left off. Delivering the speed with more precision and adding scathing female vocals as the dominant vocals that trade off with the LP's harsh male vocals, but this outing is set in an all around grimier and darker tone. This is partly from the recording, which, at times, seems at odds in trying to contain the fury. Where the LP could be described as 'metal influenced hardcore,' the metallic influences here are more incorporated into the totality of the guitar-riff blasting and squeal out as intricate bridges and curt solos. Similar to The Awakening, Memento Mori, or other bands that connect the various points between metal, the From Ashes Rise/Tragedy crust sound, and Japanese hardcore. A great exclamation point ending to a fine band that's worth getting into." --MAXIMUM ROCK'N'ROLL

name: Nightbringer - S/T 7"
description:
MOTORHEAD! MOTORHEAD! MOTORHEAD! Really love this band. This is what the label had to say about it:

Nightbringer is bastard hardcore. Taking equal parts from the holy trinity of Motorhead, 70s Detroit rock n roll, and Japanese hardcore, they land in similar hybrid territory as later Poison Idea - going back to the raw rebel rhythms that spawned biker gangs in the 50s but cranking it up with speed, distortion, and a samurai's obsession with finding life at the ever present edge of death. If punk started as youth culture, this is the sound of youths misspent in skinhead violence and skateboarding, Hawkwind-ish hallucinogens and of summers and winters in vans sleeping on amps. Carving out a niche in the wilderness to keep the fire alive into their mid 30s, this is mania focused by age and experience, never diminished. Ex Ruination, Earthmover, Life Set Struggle, and introducing Ian.

description:
Newest offering from one of my favorite labels, Deer Healer. MOTORHEAD! Seriously this record rules! Label write up:

"Motorcycle music for motorcycle people. The instrumentation is tuneful and driving, a steel pig snarling down the road with the engine open, burly hair cracking in the wind like a whip. The vocals weave and jab at the backbeat with the urgency and grace of a featherweight, but strike with all the guile and power of a thick-necked heavyweight thug. It's obvious that this band has spent a lot of time thinking about how to sound. If more bands were as thoughtful as Nightbringer, everything would just be better." - Roderick McClain

Featuring members of Earthmover, Ruination, Bloodpact, Life.Set.Struggle, etc.

name: No Comment - Common Senseless 7"
description: Reissue on Deep Six. This felt near impossible to find for a long time, critical reissue. Great record by one of my favorite bands.

name: Nukkehammer - Soviet Rust Belt 7"
description: This band is so killer. Dennis from Solar Funeral/Vile Gash/Black Dove/Hot Dog Super Lovers. If you buy anything from me, buy this. Mutant punk for fans of the hardcore.

name: Orange 9MM - Glistening 7"
description: Welp, this was from Under Dog records, and then made it to Vinyl Solution where I bought. Branden used to work there. Full circle bitches. The first 12" on Rev is legit sick. You can buy this and see what you think.

name: Pigeon Religion "Crystallized Meth" 7"
description: OOP smasher on Video Disease. Tune in drop out DIE.

name: Pollution 120608 Tape
description: Great live set and some cool covers! Amazing band!

name: Raw Nerves "Murderers Among Us" 7"
description: Debut EP from these Northwest punks. Killer shit.

name: Repercussions - No Peace 7"
description: Sick record from ex Cold Sweat dude. You are into it.

name: Revenge - Awkward 7"
description: My best buddy Sean Bong Jesus was in this band. They met me on tour outside of an insane asylum. I bought them food later. I still love this record. Silliest cover.

name: Ringworm/Terror - Split 7" white vinyl
description: HARD DUDES DUDE. Ringworm is sick as fuck. So is Terror. Scott Vogel wants you to stage dive. Todd Jones bought my guitar equipment a week or so ago. I think he was still in the band on this record. SICK DUDE.

name: The Rites - Fuck Em If They Can't Take A Joke 7"
description: SICKEST band. Buy this. Fuck you if you can't take a joke.

name: Rollins Band "Weight" Tape
description: Tape version of a SICK record.

name: Rorschach/1.6 Band - Split 7"
description: Is there really another side to this? I guess. I dunno. I saw Rorschach cover My War with Ted Leo singing. It was cool I guess. I dunno.

name: Sidetracked/Hummingbird of Death "Split" 6"
description: Great split on a ridiculous format blazing fast core from both bands. Buy or die!!!

name: Skate Korpse - S/T 7"
description: Some copy of this record. My buddy was way more into these guys than I was and I got it because he said it was great.

name: Skitsystem/Cyness - Split 7"
description: Skitsystem is sicker than Herpes. You'll dig it. Never heard the other side. Do you need to?

name: Slices "2nd" 7"
description: Second Slices 7" on Home Invasion. Killer record. Second press copies.

name: Street Trash - Five Dirty Fingers 7"
description: OC's hardest. Great record.

name: Su19b/XBrainiaX split 7"
description:
FUCKED UP NOIIIISEEEEE

not for the weak.

name: Systematic Death - Systema Seven 7"
description: On black vinyl. That's the limited color. You are stoked.

name: Take Offense "Happiness Under Chains" 7"
description:
Tough as nails 7" from Chula Vista road warriors TAKE OFFENSE. One sided 7" that reminds me a lot of the Cro-Mags and other NYHC greats. 

On the always wonderful LIFES A RAPE

name: Troops Of Tomorrow - The World Won't Listen 7"
description: It's 2011 and Garybird is moshing in space. Picked these up after eating spaghetti in DC with some nice boys. Streetpunk/OI, harsh vocals, named after the Exploited. Dope shit.

name: Unruh/Creation Is Crucifixion - Split 7"
description: GREAT record by these two bands. I think one of the better Unruh songs is on this split. Get into it.

name: Vaccuum-2nd 7"
description: Brand new 7" from these San Francisco dirty punk freeks. Great follow up to their debut on Lengua Armada, grab this if you liked the other rec or noisy/raw punk!!

name: V/A - Destroying Southern Tradition 7"
description: Comp with Suppression and I think Damad. Good comp! You'll dig it. Illest cover.

name: V/A - No Bullshit Vol 1. 7" color vinyl
description: First press color copy. Sick comp. You want it.

name: V/A - No Bullshit Vol. 3 7" color vinyl
description: Another sick comp from No Way Records. Color vinyl copy from first press. Limited. Blah blah.

name: Video Disease "Make Me Pure" 7"
description: Out of control HC. Way OOP.

name: Violent Minds "S/T" 7"
description: Reissue of the Violent Minds 7" on Deranged. punk as fuck.

name: Weak Minds - S/T 7"
description: I think this is Rahi from Insect Warfare and I'm not sure who else. It's sick though. You want it.

name: White Wards Demo II
description: 2010 demo from this cool Olympia band!

name: xBrainiax/Lettuce Vultures - Split 7"
description: xBrainiax are one of the better bands doing the No Comment style hardcore nowadays. Ex Threatener and all that, ill shit. Lettuce Vultures are the Sockeye guys blowing my mind all over again. Record is worth it for the cover art alone!

name: Brainworms - Tape
description: I have no clue what this is. Maybe you do. Buy it!

name: Bureacratic Dysentery Tape
description: One man grind band from Illinois. BRUTAL.

name: Crime Desire "S/T" CD
description: CD version of the incredible Crime Desire S/T Album. Includes the S/T LP, the ID Music To Combat the Super Ego LP, the In Lucifer's Grip 7", and a few unreleased tracks.

name: Crime Desire "We Hate All Life" CD
description: Debut CD from Crime Desire. Includes there 2003 Demo.

name: Tear It Up - Taking You Down With Me CDep
description: What a silly format the CDep ever was. It's like pressing one short song on a 33 RPM 12". For real though, this band ruled. BLACK FLAG. Any band obsessed with Black Flag is going to usually rule because Black Flag ruled.
